# [AVTCORE](../wg/avtcore.html) - IETF 125 Meeting Minutes

## Summary
The AVTCORE working group met at IETF 125 to discuss the status of active drafts, newly adopted work, and several proposals for accelerating WebRTC connection establishment. Key topics included the RTP payload format for APV, the H.265 profile for WebRTC, and the RTP Frame Acknowledgement mechanism. The group also discussed SFrame packetization and two non-chartered items (SPED and SNAP) intended to reduce round-trips in WebRTC handshakes.

## Key Discussion Points

### [AVTCore IETF 125 Chair Slides](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-avtcore-avtcore-ietf-125-chair-slides-01)
* **Chairs:** Jonathan Lennox, Marius Kleidl.
* **Minutes:** Consensus reached to use the IETF minute tool.
* **Status:** 
    * `draft-ietf-avtcore-rtcp-green-metadata` is currently in Working Group Last Call (WGLC).
    * `draft-ietf-avtcore-rtp-volumetric-media-roi` shepherd write-up is in progress.
    * `draft-ietf-avtcore-hevc-webrtc` and `draft-ietf-avtcore-rtp-apv` are active.

### [RTP payload format for APV](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-avtcore-rtp-payload-format-for-apv-00)
* **Presenter:** Sinho Mansur
* **Draft:** `draft-ietf-avtcore-rtp-apv`
* **Technical Details:** The draft covers the payload format for APV (Advanced Professional Video). It supports "Simple Mode" (MTU-based fragmentation) and "Low Delay Mode" (tile boundary alignment).
* **Discussion:**
    * Mo Zanaty suggested renaming the "payload type" field in the APV header to avoid confusion with the RTP Payload Type field.
    * Jonathan Lennox raised concerns regarding the 16-bit sequence number at high bitrates (hundreds of Mbps) and suggested investigating an extended sequence number to prevent premature wrap-around.

### [H.265 Profile for WebRTC](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-avtcore-h265-profile-for-webrtc-00)
* **Presenter:** Philipp Hancke
* **Draft:** `draft-ietf-avtcore-hevc-webrtc`
* **Updates:** Jianlin (Intel) joined as co-author. HEVC in WebRTC has shipped in Chrome 136 (hardware) and Safari 18.
* **Discussion:** Mo Zanaty confirmed that WebRTC implementations use in-band parameter sets on keyframes. Philipp Hancke noted that while Reference Picture Selection Indication (RPSI) is specified, it is not yet implemented in browsers.

### [RTP Payload Format for Avatar Representation Format (ARF) Animation Stream](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-avtcore-rtp-payload-format-for-avatar-representation-format-arf-animation-stream-00)
* **Presenter:** (Author team)
* **Draft:** `draft-ietf-avtcore-rtp-avatar`
* **Updates:** The draft has been updated to align terminology with MPEG specifications.
* **Next Steps:** The authors plan to request WGLC once the MPEG Avatar specification reaches the FDIS (Final Draft International Standard) stage.

### [RTP Frame Acknowledgement version 2](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-avtcore-rtp-frame-acknowledgement-version-2-00)
* **Presenter:** Gurtej Singh
* **Draft:** `draft-ietf-avtcore-rtp-frame-acknowledgement`
* **Technical Details:** Provides a codec-agnostic feedback mechanism for senders to identify which frames were successfully decoded, allowing for precise reference frame selection. Added a receiver-triggered resynchronization request.
* **Discussion:**
    * Mo Zanaty and Stephan Wenger expressed concerns regarding whether a generic mechanism can truly be codec-agnostic without specific bindings for AV1, H.264, or H.265.
    * Eric Rescorla noted that the mechanism relies on the sender knowing the bitstream; the receiver just needs to report what it successfully processed.
    * A sense of the room indicated support for adoption.

### [SFrame RTP Packetization](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-avtcore-sframe-rtp-packetization-00)
* **Presenter:** Youenn Fablet
* **Draft:** `draft-ietf-avtcore-rtp-sframe`
* **Updates:** Added a 'T' (Type) bit to distinguish between raw (WebRTC encoded transform) and pre-packetized content. Introduced per-SSRC key derivation for Matter (CHIP) use cases.
* **Discussion:** Implementation is underway in `libdatachannel` and planned for `libwebrtc`. Goal is to reach WGLC by the end of the year.

### [STUN Protocol for Embedding DTLS](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-avtcore-stun-protocol-for-embedding-dtls-00)
* **Presenter:** Justin Uberti
* **Summary:** Proposed embedding DTLS handshake packets within STUN attributes during ICE connectivity checks to save 1-2 RTTs. 
* **Discussion:** Harald Alvestrand noted that Google is implementing a similar mechanism. The chairs will coordinate with TSVWG to determine the appropriate home for this work.

### [SCTP Negotiation Acceleration Protocol](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-avtcore-sctp-negotiation-acceleration-protocol-01)
* **Presenter:** Philipp Hancke
* **Summary:** Proposes carrying the SCTP INIT/INIT-ACK chunks within SDP to allow data channels to be ready immediately after the DTLS handshake.
* **Discussion:** Magnus Westerlund and Jonathan Lennox discussed potential issues with SDP forking and `PRANSWER`. While the SCTP changes are minimal, the SDP mapping requires careful review. 

